comment: Comes here in top form and effective under the conditions; high on the list
spotlight: Registered first handicap success at Chelmsford last month and followed it with a good second at Yarmouth in week one of the Racing League (5f, soft); has solid C&D form and he's respected despite edging up the weights.

comment: Two solid efforts to start her life with this yard but disappointed at York last week
spotlight: Three wins for Michael Bell, two of them on AW; two promising runs to start off her time with Iain Jardine but she finished weakly at York last week; due to be 2lb lower from the weekend.

comment: High-class on his day, including 3-4 on AW; big player if he consents to start on time
spotlight: High-class sprinter on his day and he has tasted defeat in just one of his four runs on AW; fine effort to beat Marshman in a Listed race here in February and third in a Newmarket Group 3 next time; no doubt he has the ability to win a race of this nature but he is increasingly troublesome at the start and he has refused to race twice this summer; capable but too much risk attached to recommend.

comment: Close 4th in this race last year; absent until down the field at York last week; opposable
spotlight: Beaten 1l into fourth in this race 12 months ago (off this mark); absent until finishing down the field at York last week; due to be 3lb lower in the future and he needs to have come on a good deal in a short space of time.
